%text If $f(x)$ be a polynomial, then $f(x)$ is of the form \[a_0 + a_1 x + a_2 x^2 + \ldots + a_n x^n = \sum_{k=1}^n a_k\cdot x^k\] And for such an $f(x)$ (a polynomial) \[\qquad \qquad \lim_{x\to a}f(x) = f(a) \] Below are two examples using two polynomials and limits for when $x\to 1$
% \begin{align} \begin{tabular}{MM}
\hline f(x) & \lim_{x\to 1}f(x) = f(1) \\ \hline x^2-7x+89 & \lim_{x\to 1}(x^2-7x+89) = 83 \\ \hline x^5-26x& \lim_{x\to 1}(x^5-26x)= -25 \\ \hline \end{tabular} \end{align} %text %
